<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="some-adj">some <strong><em>adj</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /səm,sʌm/    美 /səm,sʌm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[多用于肯定句，与不可数名词或可数名词复数连用] 若干的；一些的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You left some money on the table.
你把钱落在桌子上了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>May I help you? You seem to be having some problems.
有什么需要帮忙的吗？你好像碰到了一些麻烦事。</p><footer>2012 安徽</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[用于疑问句，希望得到肯定的回答或表示建议、请求等] 一些；一点：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Would you have some tea?
喝点儿茶吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Aren’t there some envelopes in that drawer?
那个抽屉里不是还有几个信封吗？</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[用于可数名词单数之前，表示未知或说话人不想说明的事物等] 某个；某一：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>in some way
以某种方式</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>for some reason
由于某种原因</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Some person at the door is asking to see you.
门口有个人要见你。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="some-more">some more</h3>
<p>1.<strong>再多点 (的)；再多些 (的)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Have some more bread; it’ll make you feel much better
再吃些面包，那样你会感觉好一些。</p></div>

<h3 id="some-or-other">some ... or other</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[用于表示不肯定或不精确] 某一：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve read about it before in some book or other. 
我以前曾在某一本书里读到过与此有关的内容。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Don’t worry if you can’t come to <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ party — I’ll save <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ cake for you.<br />
A.the; some<br />
B.a; much<br />
C.the; any<br />
D.a; little  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. A  </p></div>